data.title: The Sheed Show
data.meta_description: When Rasheed Wallace’s name was announced during pregame introductions Wednesday night, “Sheeeeeed” bellowed through The Palace. The fans’ reaction was neither as hostile as Ben Wallace’s return as a Chicago Bull in 2007, nor as exultant as Chauncey Billups’ return as a Denver Nugget last March. But it was a loss, which put Wallace in familiar company. He became the third starter from the Pistons’ 2004 championship team to lose his first game back at The Palace.
